  "text": "paratus [CITATION_1] Uprety 1993, Flexas et al. 2012) . Lack of sunlight (solar radiation) usually causes photoinhibition (light-induced decline in photochemical activity) [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . It is reported that photosynthesis is significantly inhibited at both low and high temperatures, which usually resulted in an impaired photosynthetic apparatus and a depressed photosynthetic capacity [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] .",
